headline: These High-Yielding Dividend Stocks are Already in the $1 Trillion Club and Have Plenty of Room to Keep Growing
summary: Brookfield Asset Management (NYSE: BAM) and Blackstone Group (NYSE: BX) are two of the biggest alternative asset managers in the world.  Each has already surpassed the milestone of having $1 trillion in assets under management (AUM).  Brookfield's payout yields 3.6%, while Blackstone's yield is 2.4%.
